title: Foal Hurst Wood
text:
Foal Hurst Wood is a <a href="Local%20Nature%20Reserve">Local Nature Reserve</a> on the south-western outskirts of <a href="Paddock%20Wood">Paddock Wood</a> in <a href="Kent">Kent</a>. It is owned by <a href="Tunbridge%20Wells%20Borough%20Council">Tunbridge Wells Borough Council</a> and managed by Paddock Wood Town Council.
This site is mainly coppiced woodland and there is grassland at the northern end. Birds include <a href="European%20green%20woodpecker">green</a> and <a href="great%20spotted%20woodpecker">great spotted woodpecker</a>s, and there are flora such as orchids.
There is access from Badsell Road.
